29/*
30 * This contains a mutex, but it's pretty convenient to allow the mutex code to
31 * have a dependency on tsd. So we define the struct here, and only refer to it
32 * by pointer in the header.
33 */
34struct tsd_init_head_s {
35 ql_head(tsd_init_block_t) blocks;
36 malloc_mutex_t lock;
37};
38
39pthread_key_t tsd_tsd;
40tsd_init_head_t tsd_init_head = {
41 ql_head_initializer(blocks),
42#ifndef __lint__
43 // XXX: broken lint
44 MALLOC_MUTEX_INITIALIZER
45#endif
46};
47tsd_wrapper_t tsd_boot_wrapper = {
48 false,
49 TSD_INITIALIZER
50};
51bool tsd_booted = false;
52#endif

57void
58tsd_slow_update(tsd_t *tsd) {
59 if (tsd_nominal(tsd)) {
60 if (malloc_slow || !tsd_tcache_enabled_get(tsd) ||
61 tsd_reentrancy_level_get(tsd) > 0) {
62 tsd->state = tsd_state_nominal_slow;
63 } else {
64 tsd->state = tsd_state_nominal;
65 }
66 }
67}
68
69static bool
70tsd_data_init(tsd_t *tsd) {
71 /*
72 * We initialize the rtree context first (before the tcache), since the
73 * tcache initialization depends on it.
74 */
75 rtree_ctx_data_init(tsd_rtree_ctxp_get_unsafe(tsd));
76
77 /*
78 * A nondeterministic seed based on the address of tsd reduces
79 * the likelihood of lockstep non-uniform cache index
80 * utilization among identical concurrent processes, but at the
81 * cost of test repeatability. For debug builds, instead use a
82 * deterministic seed.
83 */
84 *tsd_offset_statep_get(tsd) = config_debug ? 0 :
85 (uint64_t)(uintptr_t)tsd;
86
87 return tsd_tcache_enabled_data_init(tsd);
88}
89
90static void
91assert_tsd_data_cleanup_done(tsd_t *tsd) {
92 assert(!tsd_nominal(tsd));
93 assert(*tsd_arenap_get_unsafe(tsd) == NULL);
94 assert(*tsd_iarenap_get_unsafe(tsd) == NULL);
95 assert(*tsd_arenas_tdata_bypassp_get_unsafe(tsd) == true);
96 assert(*tsd_arenas_tdatap_get_unsafe(tsd) == NULL);
97 assert(*tsd_tcache_enabledp_get_unsafe(tsd) == false);
98 assert(*tsd_prof_tdatap_get_unsafe(tsd) == NULL);
99}
100
101static bool
102tsd_data_init_nocleanup(tsd_t *tsd) {
103 assert(tsd->state == tsd_state_reincarnated ||
104 tsd->state == tsd_state_minimal_initialized);
105 /*
106 * During reincarnation, there is no guarantee that the cleanup function
107 * will be called (deallocation may happen after all tsd destructors).
108 * We set up tsd in a way that no cleanup is needed.
109 */
110 rtree_ctx_data_init(tsd_rtree_ctxp_get_unsafe(tsd));
111 *tsd_arenas_tdata_bypassp_get(tsd) = true;
112 *tsd_tcache_enabledp_get_unsafe(tsd) = false;
113 *tsd_reentrancy_levelp_get(tsd) = 1;
114 assert_tsd_data_cleanup_done(tsd);
115
116 return false;
117}
118
119tsd_t *
120tsd_fetch_slow(tsd_t *tsd, bool minimal) {
121 assert(!tsd_fast(tsd));
122
123 if (tsd->state == tsd_state_nominal_slow) {
124 /* On slow path but no work needed. */
125 assert(malloc_slow || !tsd_tcache_enabled_get(tsd) ||
126 tsd_reentrancy_level_get(tsd) > 0 ||
127 *tsd_arenas_tdata_bypassp_get(tsd));
128 } else if (tsd->state == tsd_state_uninitialized) {
129 if (!minimal) {
130 tsd->state = tsd_state_nominal;
131 tsd_slow_update(tsd);
132 /* Trigger cleanup handler registration. */
133 tsd_set(tsd);
134 tsd_data_init(tsd);
135 } else {
136 tsd->state = tsd_state_minimal_initialized;
137 tsd_set(tsd);
138 tsd_data_init_nocleanup(tsd);
139 }
140 } else if (tsd->state == tsd_state_minimal_initialized) {
141 if (!minimal) {
142 /* Switch to fully initialized. */
143 tsd->state = tsd_state_nominal;
144 assert(*tsd_reentrancy_levelp_get(tsd) >= 1);
145 (*tsd_reentrancy_levelp_get(tsd))--;
146 tsd_slow_update(tsd);
147 tsd_data_init(tsd);
148 } else {
149 assert_tsd_data_cleanup_done(tsd);
150 }
151 } else if (tsd->state == tsd_state_purgatory) {
152 tsd->state = tsd_state_reincarnated;
153 tsd_set(tsd);
154 tsd_data_init_nocleanup(tsd);
155 } else {
156 assert(tsd->state == tsd_state_reincarnated);
157 }
158
159 return tsd;
160}

172#if defined(JEMALLOC_MALLOC_THREAD_CLEANUP) || defined(_WIN32)
173#ifndef _WIN32
174JEMALLOC_EXPORT
175#endif
176void
177_malloc_thread_cleanup(void) {
178 bool pending[MALLOC_TSD_CLEANUPS_MAX], again;
179 unsigned i;
180
181 for (i = 0; i < ncleanups; i++) {
182 pending[i] = true;
183 }
184
185 do {
186 again = false;
187 for (i = 0; i < ncleanups; i++) {
188 if (pending[i]) {
189 pending[i] = cleanups[i]();
190 if (pending[i]) {
191 again = true;
192 }
193 }
194 }
195 } while (again);
196}
197#endif
198
199void
200malloc_tsd_cleanup_register(bool (*f)(void)) {
201 assert(ncleanups < MALLOC_TSD_CLEANUPS_MAX);
202 cleanups[ncleanups] = f;
203 ncleanups++;
204}
205
206static void
207tsd_do_data_cleanup(tsd_t *tsd) {
208 prof_tdata_cleanup(tsd);
209 iarena_cleanup(tsd);
210 arena_cleanup(tsd);
211 arenas_tdata_cleanup(tsd);
212 tcache_cleanup(tsd);
213 witnesses_cleanup(tsd_witness_tsdp_get_unsafe(tsd));
214}
215
216void
217tsd_cleanup(void *arg) {
218 tsd_t *tsd = (tsd_t *)arg;
219
220 switch (tsd->state) {
221 case tsd_state_uninitialized:
222 /* Do nothing. */
223 break;
224 case tsd_state_minimal_initialized:
225 /* This implies the thread only did free() in its life time. */
226 /* Fall through. */
227 case tsd_state_reincarnated:
228 /*
229 * Reincarnated means another destructor deallocated memory
230 * after the destructor was called. Cleanup isn't required but
231 * is still called for testing and completeness.
232 */
233 assert_tsd_data_cleanup_done(tsd);
234 /* Fall through. */
235 case tsd_state_nominal:
236 case tsd_state_nominal_slow:
237 tsd_do_data_cleanup(tsd);
238 tsd->state = tsd_state_purgatory;
239 tsd_set(tsd);
240 break;
241 case tsd_state_purgatory:
242 /*
243 * The previous time this destructor was called, we set the
244 * state to tsd_state_purgatory so that other destructors
245 * wouldn't cause re-creation of the tsd. This time, do
246 * nothing, and do not request another callback.
247 */
248 break;
249 default:
250 not_reached();
251 }
252#ifdef JEMALLOC_JET
253 test_callback_t test_callback = *tsd_test_callbackp_get_unsafe(tsd);
254 int *data = tsd_test_datap_get_unsafe(tsd);
255 if (test_callback != NULL) {
256 test_callback(data);
257 }
258#endif
259}
260
261tsd_t *
262malloc_tsd_boot0(void) {
263 tsd_t *tsd;
264
265 ncleanups = 0;
266 if (tsd_boot0()) {
267 return NULL;
268 }
269 tsd = tsd_fetch();
270 *tsd_arenas_tdata_bypassp_get(tsd) = true;
271 return tsd;
272}
273
274void
275malloc_tsd_boot1(void) {
276 tsd_boot1();
277 tsd_t *tsd = tsd_fetch();
278 /* malloc_slow has been set properly. Update tsd_slow. */
279 tsd_slow_update(tsd);
280 *tsd_arenas_tdata_bypassp_get(tsd) = false;
281}

283#ifdef _WIN32
284static BOOL WINAPI
285_tls_callback(HINSTANCE hinstDLL, DWORD fdwReason, LPVOID lpvReserved) {
286 switch (fdwReason) {
287#ifdef JEMALLOC_LAZY_LOCK
288 case DLL_THREAD_ATTACH:
289 isthreaded = true;
290 break;
291#endif
292 case DLL_THREAD_DETACH:
293 _malloc_thread_cleanup();
294 break;
295 default:
296 break;
297 }
298 return true;
299}

301/*
302 * We need to be able to say "read" here (in the "pragma section"), but have
303 * hooked "read". We won't read for the rest of the file, so we can get away
304 * with unhooking.
305 */
306#ifdef read
307# undef read
308#endif
309
310#ifdef _MSC_VER
311# ifdef _M_IX86
312# pragma comment(linker, "/INCLUDE:__tls_used")
313# pragma comment(linker, "/INCLUDE:_tls_callback")
314# else
315# pragma comment(linker, "/INCLUDE:_tls_used")
316# pragma comment(linker, "/INCLUDE:tls_callback")
317# endif
318# pragma section(".CRT$XLY",long,read)
319#endif
320JEMALLOC_SECTION(".CRT$XLY") JEMALLOC_ATTR(used)
321BOOL (WINAPI *const tls_callback)(HINSTANCE hinstDLL,
322 DWORD fdwReason, LPVOID lpvReserved) = _tls_callback;
323#endif

325#if (!defined(JEMALLOC_MALLOC_THREAD_CLEANUP) && !defined(JEMALLOC_TLS) && \
326 !defined(_WIN32))
327void *
328tsd_init_check_recursion(tsd_init_head_t *head, tsd_init_block_t *block) {
329 pthread_t self = pthread_self();
330 tsd_init_block_t *iter;
331
332 /* Check whether this thread has already inserted into the list. */
333 malloc_mutex_lock(TSDN_NULL, &head->lock);
334 ql_foreach(iter, &head->blocks, link) {
335 if (iter->thread == self) {
336 malloc_mutex_unlock(TSDN_NULL, &head->lock);
337 return iter->data;
338 }
339 }
340 /* Insert block into list. */
341 ql_elm_new(block, link);
342 block->thread = self;
343 ql_tail_insert(&head->blocks, block, link);
344 malloc_mutex_unlock(TSDN_NULL, &head->lock);
345 return NULL;
346}
347
348void
349tsd_init_finish(tsd_init_head_t *head, tsd_init_block_t *block) {
350 malloc_mutex_lock(TSDN_NULL, &head->lock);
351 ql_remove(&head->blocks, block, link);
352 malloc_mutex_unlock(TSDN_NULL, &head->lock);
353}
354#endif
